  "title": "Data Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary:</strong></p><p>We are looking for an experienced <strong>Operations Lead </strong>to manage support operations for <strong>Cloudera</strong> and <strong>Informatica </strong>platforms. The role involves incident management, monthly reporting, and ensuring processes are run as per SOPs.<br /></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Act as <strong>Incident Manager</strong> to ensure timely resolution based on severity and SLAs.</li><li>Drive <strong>monthly reporting</strong> on operational KPIs and issues.</li><li>Ensure operations are aligned with <strong>SOPs</strong> and best practices.</li><li>Provide <strong>expert support</strong> on Cloudera and Informatica platforms.</li><li>Lead or support <strong>platform upgrades</strong> (Cloudera/Informatica).</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>5+ years</strong> of experience in Cloudera & Informatica (BDM) operations and upgrades.</li><li>Strong knowledge of <strong>incident management</strong> and <strong>support processes</strong>.</li><li>Strong knowledge in assessing risk and remediating security findings (Vulnerability assessment)</li><li>Experience in <strong>platform upgrades</strong> and post-upgrade validation.</li><li>Good communication and stakeholder management skills.</li><li>ITIL knowledge/certification is a plus.</li></ul>",
